  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison writes to Theodore Parker: &quot;I am greatly obliged to you for your kind note,---so characteristic of your catholic spirit in all matters pertaining to an honest and conscientious difference of opinion.&quot; Garrison will not accept payment for his speech (to Parker&apos;s congregation). Garrison considers himself indebted to Parker, especially for his &quot;consoling services in times of affliction and bereavement by death.&quot;</subfield>
